                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I only know I was sent for, and found this money upon him, three shillings and two sixpences; I produce the money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850112-18-person289">
                  JOHN
                   BRATHWAITE
               <interp inst="t17850112-18-person289" type="surname" value="BRATHWAITE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850112-18-person289" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850112-18-person289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I was in a little room adjoining to the shop, I saw a man go behind the compter, who I suspected to be a thief, I pursued him and brought him back.</p>
               <p>Mrs. Ford. I swear positively to that.</p>
               <p>When did you count your money before? - About half an hour before; I had lost some butter, that caused me to count my money.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was coming down Compton-street, and they took me to a chandler's shop, and said I had robbed the shop, my mother goes out to chair work.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850112-18-verdict105" type="verdictDescription">
